@page "/"

<PageTitle>Predictive Maintenance using Artificial Intelligence</PageTitle>

<div class="splash">
    <section class="hero">
        <div class="hero-badge">⚙️ Predictive Maintenance using Artificial Intelligence</div>
        <h1 class="hero-title">Stop failures before they happen.</h1>
        <p class="hero-lead">
            This dashboard turns raw maintenance logs, breakdown tickets, machines and spare-parts
            data into a single, explainable <strong>risk score per machine</strong> &mdash; so teams
            know exactly what to service next, and why.
        </p>
        <div class="hero-actions">
            <a class="btn btn-primary btn-lg" href="dashboard">Open the dashboard &rarr;</a>
            <a class="btn btn-outline-secondary btn-lg" href="rules">See the rules</a>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
        <h2 class="section-title">How it works</h2>
        <div class="row g-3">
            <div class="col-md-6 col-xl-3">
                <div class="feature-card">
                    <div class="feature-icon">🔗</div>
                    <h3>1. Join the data</h3>
                    <p>Maintenance logs, tickets, machines and spare parts are joined together so every
                        downtime event is attributed to a real machine.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-6 col-xl-3">
                <div class="feature-card">
                    <div class="feature-icon">📏</div>
                    <h3>2. Score with rules</h3>
                    <p>A <strong>rules engine</strong> applies weighted, editable business rules
                        (overdue maintenance, frequent tickets, high downtime).</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-6 col-xl-3">
                <div class="feature-card">
                    <div class="feature-icon">🤖</div>
                    <h3>3. Predict with Machine Learning</h3>
                    <p>The <strong>model</strong> continously learns from the history, turns those
                        signals into a failure probability, blended 55/45 with the rule score.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-6 col-xl-3">
                <div class="feature-card">
                    <div class="feature-icon">🧠</div>
                    <h3>4. Explain with AI</h3>
                    <p><strong>Generative AI</strong> writes a plain-language recommendation for each
                        high-risk machine and an overall fleet summary.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
        <h2 class="section-title">Why it's useful</h2>
        <div class="row g-3">
            <div class="col-md-6">
                <ul class="value-list">
                    <li><strong>Cut unplanned downtime.</strong> Surface at-risk assets before they fail
                        instead of reacting to breakdowns.</li>
                    <li><strong>Prioritize limited crews.</strong> A ranked, severity-tagged list tells a
                        small team what to service first.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-6">
                <ul class="value-list">
                    <li><strong>Plan spare parts.</strong> Repeated high-downtime parts and lead times flag
                        supply-chain risk early.</li>
                    <li><strong>Explainable, not a black box.</strong> Every score can show its rule factors,
                        ML probability, and an AI rationale.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <div class="cta-footer">
        <a class="btn btn-primary btn-lg" href="dashboard">Launch the dashboard &rarr;</a>
        <div class="mt-3">
            <a class="text-muted small" href="about">About the developer</a>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
